<!--
  This XML is a negative example because it is semantically incorrect and represents a flawed conversion that causes runtime errors.

  REASONS FOR BEING A NEGATIVE EXAMPLE:

  1.  CRITICAL: Incorrect Interaction Behavior (`min-choices`/`max-choices`) - The Perseus source is a simple "sorter" widget where the user must arrange a fixed set of three cards. This QTI incorrectly uses `min-choices="3"` and `max-choices="3"` on the <qti-order-interaction>. These attributes are for tasks where the user must first *select a subset* of choices and then order them. By setting them here, the interaction's behavior is fundamentally changed, requiring the user to first select all three cards before ordering is possible. This misrepresents the original task and causes confusing validation errors, such as ("You must set the order for at least 3 choices for this question."), because the system is waiting for a selection step that the user interface may not even support for this simple arrangement. For a simple "arrange all items" task, these attributes should have been omitted.
  2.  CRITICAL: Loss of Mathematical Semantics in Feedback - The feedback blocks render the comparison "42 < 411" as plain text with a non-breaking space ("42 < 411"). This is semantically incorrect. All mathematical content, including in feedback, should be wrapped in <math> tags with proper MathML markup to ensure accessibility and correct rendering by math-aware systems.
-->
<qti-assessment-item
    xmlns="http://www.imsglobal.org/xsd/imsqtiasi_v3p0"
    xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance"
    xsi:schemaLocation="http://www.imsglobal.org/xsd/imsqtiasi_v3p0 https://purl.imsglobal.org/spec/qti/v3p0/schema/xsd/imsqti_asiv3p0p1_v1p0.xsd http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML https://purl.imsglobal.org/spec/mathml/v3p0/schema/xsd/mathml3.xsd"
    identifier="nice-tmp:xe203472ed1d4f092"
    title="Compare 3-digit numbers"
    time-dependent="false"
    xml:lang="en-US">

    <qti-response-declaration identifier="RESPONSE" cardinality="ordered" base-type="identifier">
        <qti-correct-response>
            <qti-value>A</qti-value>
            <qti-value>B</qti-value>
            <qti-value>C</qti-value>
        </qti-correct-response>
    </qti-response-declaration>

    <qti-outcome-declaration identifier="FEEDBACK" cardinality="single" base-type="identifier"/>
    <qti-outcome-declaration identifier="FEEDBACK-INLINE" cardinality="single" base-type="identifier"/>

    <qti-item-body>
        <qti-order-interaction response-identifier="RESPONSE" shuffle="true" max-choices="3" min-choices="3" orientation="horizontal">
            <qti-prompt>Arrange the cards to make a true comparison.</qti-prompt>
            <qti-simple-choice identifier="A">
                <math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><mn>42</mn></math>
                <qti-feedback-inline outcome-identifier="FEEDBACK-INLINE" identifier="A">42 is the smaller number, so it belongs on the left side of a less-than comparison.</qti-feedback-inline>
            </qti-simple-choice>
            <qti-simple-choice identifier="B">
                <math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><mo><</mo></math>
                <qti-feedback-inline outcome-identifier="FEEDBACK-INLINE" identifier="B">The symbol “<” indicates that the value on the left is less than the value on the right.</qti-feedback-inline>
            </qti-simple-choice>
            <qti-simple-choice identifier="C">
                <math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><mn>411</mn></math>
                <qti-feedback-inline outcome-identifier="FEEDBACK-INLINE" identifier="C">411 is the larger number, so it belongs on the right side of the comparison.</qti-feedback-inline>
            </qti-simple-choice>
        </qti-order-interaction>

        <qti-feedback-block outcome-identifier="FEEDBACK" identifier="CORRECT" show-hide="show">
            <qti-content-body>
                <p><strong>Correct!</strong> The comparison 42 < 411 is true because 42 is less than 411.</p>
            </qti-content-body>
        </qti-feedback-block>
        <qti-feedback-block outcome-identifier="FEEDBACK" identifier="INCORRECT" show-hide="show">
            <qti-content-body>
                <p><strong>Not quite.</strong> Remember, 42 is less than 411, so the “less-than” symbol (<math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><mo><</mo></math>) should point toward the smaller number.</p>
            </qti-content-body>
        </qti-feedback-block>
    </qti-item-body>

    <qti-response-processing template="https://purl.imsglobal.org/spec/qti/v3p0/rptemplates/match_correct"/>

</qti-assessment-item>